### 2.2 Build Profile Purposes

#### **development**
- **Purpose:** Local testing with dev client
- **Output:** Development build (can load bundles from Expo CLI)
- **Simulator:** iOS simulator build (faster, for testing)
- **When to use:** Active development

**Build command:**
```bash
eas build --profile development --platform ios
```

---

#### **preview**
- **Purpose:** QA testing on real devices via TestFlight (iOS) and APK sideload (Android)
- **API Target:** Dev AWS (`https://d1twtjfgg5e272.cloudfront.net/graphql`)
- **Output:** TestFlight build (iOS), APK (Android)
- **Distribution:** Internal testers only
- **Build:** Local (`--local` flag) -- NOT EAS cloud
- **When to use:** Day-to-day QA testing, stakeholder demos, beta testing
- **Google Sign-In:** Not available (client IDs not configured for dev backend)
- **Crash Reporting:** Enabled (same Sentry DSN as production)

**Build command:**
```bash
eas build --profile preview --platform ios --local
```

---

#### **production**
- **Purpose:** App Store and Google Play release
- **Output:** App Store IPA, Google Play AAB
- **Auto-increment:** Build number increments automatically
- **When to use:** Production releases

**Build command:**
```bash
eas build --profile production --platform all
```

